  under the russian empire thumb|"soldier and sailor " memorial to heroic defenders of sevastopol thumb|upright|the monument to the ships scuttled during the siege of sevastopol during the crimean war by amandus adamson   sevastopol was founded in june 1783 as a base for a naval squadron under the name akhtiar ( white cliff ) , by rear admiral thomas mackenzie ( foma fomich makenzi ) , a native scot in russian service ; soon after russia annexed the crimean khanate .

